Buchloe dactyloides

   [3961.jpg]
    Authority   (Nutt.) Engelm.
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms
   Common names buffalo grass, sesleria, antofora
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 3961

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A low growing grass spreading by numerous stolons and
   forming a dense sod. USES Used as a forage grass and as ground cover.
   GROWING PERIOD Perennial. It furnishes excellent forage year-round.
   COMMON NAMES Buffalo grass. FURTHER INF It provides good cover for
   exposed dry banks.

   Sources
   SOURCES (B. dactyloides (Nutt.) Engelm.)
   Heath M 1985 pp 181 [TEXT, DRA, USE]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 146 [USE, DRA, LIG]
   Duke J 1979 pp 94 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]

